<task id="011" project="sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair">
  <metadata>
    <title>P1.A2 — Repair Communications compile-broken files (Archival, Association, Attachment, Communication, Dataverse)</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>2-2.5 hours</estimated-effort>
    <assigned>AI agent</assigned>
    <tags>phase-1, compile-fix, bff-api, testing, p1-a, communications, sibling-coordination</tags>
    <parallel-group>1-A</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>5 disjoint files all under Services/Communication/; no overlap with batches 010, 012, 013, 015, 017, 020, 021, 022, 024</parallel-reason>
    <rigor>FULL</rigor>
    <repair-not-rewrite>true</repair-not-rewrite>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Repair 5 compile-broken test files in `Services/Communication/` from the design.md §3.2 list.
    These files have the HIGHEST sibling-coordination risk per design.md §2.3 — the
    `x-email-communication-solution-r2` project owner is the source authority for any signature
    changes in Communications production code.

    COORDINATION (binding): Before editing, verify owner of `x-email-communication-solution-r2`
    has not changed the underlying production signatures since the 2026-05-30 baseline. If
    Communications production code shipped a NEW signature change after baseline, surface in
    `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/current-task.md` and pause for owner confirmation.

    Per NFR-02: repair only; &gt;50% replacement requires §4.8 escalation. Per NFR-01: NO
    production code changes.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET test repair specialist coordinated with `x-email-communication-solution-r2` owner.</role>

  <goal>
    The 5 Communications test files compile cleanly under `dotnet build -warnaserror`. Coordination
    note recorded in `current-task.md` confirming alignment with Communications project owner.
    Every touched test has `[Trait("status", "repaired")]`. Build error count drops by ~30-40.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="baseline">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/compile-errors-2026-MM-DD.txt</file>
    <file purpose="target-1">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Communication/ArchivalFlowTests.cs</file>
    <file purpose="target-2">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Communication/AssociationMappingTests.cs</file>
    <file purpose="target-3">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Communication/AttachmentValidationTests.cs</file>
    <file purpose="target-4">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Communication/CommunicationServiceTests.cs</file>
    <file purpose="target-5">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Communication/DataverseRecordCreationTests.cs</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">MUST NOT modify production code in `src/Services/Communication/`</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-02">MUST NOT replace &gt;50% of any file without §4.8 escalation</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-11">All files compile under `-warnaserror` after repair</constraint>
    <constraint source="§6.2">Every touched test gets `[Trait("status", "repaired")]`</constraint>
    <constraint source="§4.7 + §2.3">Coordinate with `x-email-communication-solution-r2` owner BEFORE editing</constraint>
    <constraint source="§4.5">MUST NOT touch `CustomWebAppFactory.cs`</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per design.md §2.3 the Communications-related test files are the HIGHEST sibling-coordination
      risk in the compile-broken set. The sibling project `x-email-communication-solution-r2` is
      actively iterating on Communications production code; signature drift in this batch is
      likely driven by their work. Aligning with their owner BEFORE editing prevents this batch
      from being re-broken by their next merge.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="001" status="not-started">Baseline TRX + compile-errors log produced</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Communication/ArchivalFlowTests.cs</file>
    <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Communication/AssociationMappingTests.cs</file>
    <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Communication/AttachmentValidationTests.cs</file>
    <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Communication/CommunicationServiceTests.cs</file>
    <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Communication/DataverseRecordCreationTests.cs</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Coordinate with `x-email-communication-solution-r2` owner: confirm no in-flight production signature changes will land in `Services/Communication/` within the next 24h. Record outcome in `current-task.md` Decisions section.</step>
    <step order="2">Read the 5 target files. For each, identify SUT and inspect current `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Communication/` constructor signatures.</step>
    <step order="3">Classify each compile error: CS7036 (add missing arg with fake/mock), CS1503 (cast to expected type), CS1061 (rename in production → update call site).</step>
    <step order="4">Compute pre-edit line counts. If any planned edit exceeds 50% → HALT and file `escalations/rewrite-request-T-011-{FileName}.md`.</step>
    <step order="5">Apply edits one file at a time; run `dotnet build` after each and confirm error drop.</step>
    <step order="6">Add `[Trait("status", "repaired")]` to every touched test class.</step>
    <step order="7">Final compile gate: `dotnet build tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ -c Release -warnaserror` returns 0 on the 5 target files.</step>
    <step order="8">Update `current-task.md` with coordination outcome + per-file LOC delta + new error total.</step>
    <step order="9">Verify `git status` shows NO modifications under `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">build</tool>
    <tool name="git">status</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Communication/ArchivalFlowTests.cs (repaired)</output>
    <output type="code">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Communication/AssociationMappingTests.cs (repaired)</output>
    <output type="code">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Communication/AttachmentValidationTests.cs (repaired)</output>
    <output type="code">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Communication/CommunicationServiceTests.cs (repaired)</output>
    <output type="code">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Communication/DataverseRecordCreationTests.cs (repaired)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/current-task.md (coordination note)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">All 5 files compile under `dotnet build -c Release -warnaserror`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Coordination note with `x-email-communication-solution-r2` owner recorded in `current-task.md`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Build error count drops by ~30-40 vs Phase 0 baseline</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Per-file diff &lt;50% line replacement; if exceeded, escalation file exists</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Every touched test has `[Trait("status", "repaired")]`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No modifications to `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`CustomWebAppFactory.cs` NOT modified</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
